article.description: — Josh Oduro had 31 points as George Mason got past Saint Joseph's 77-71 on Monday night.
article.headline: Oduro lifts George Mason past Saint Joseph's 77-71
article.linkText: Oduro lifts George Mason past Saint Joseph's 77-71
article.story: FAIRFAX, Va. -- — Josh Oduro had 31 points as George Mason got past Saint Joseph's 77-71 on Monday night. D'Shawn Schwartz had 14 points for George Mason (9-7, 2-1 Atlantic 10 Conference). Davonte Gaines added nine rebounds. Erik Reynolds II had 18 points for the Hawks (8-10, 2-5). Taylor Funk added 17 points. Jordan Hall had 15 points, nine rebounds and nine assists. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
